@NODE introduction


        INTRODUCTION

        Haven't  you also been jealous of the PC owners with all their
        mouse  drivers?   You  don't  have to anymore, because here is 
        what you all have been waiting for!  
        A MOUSE DRIVER FOR THE AMIGA.

        This  mouse  driver is compatible with all known Amiga mouses.
        All you have to do is to install it in your startup-sequence.

@ENDNODE

@NODE system

        SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS

        Mouse  requires at least AmigaOS 1.0 and a WORKING Amiga (It's
        works  best  if  the  Amiga  is turned on.).  You also need at
        least one diskdrive but a harddisk is recommended. If you have
        a  68030  or  a  68040 the mouse doesn't go faster.  Mouse has
        been tested on:
        
        Amiga 500 1 MB ram 10 MB hd
        Amiga 500+ 3 MB ram 11 MB hd
        Amiga 500+ 68030 25mhz 5 MB ram 45 MB hd
        Amiga 2000 
        and a few other configurations

@ENDNODE

@NODE instalation

        INSTALATION
        
        Just copy it to your C: directory ans run it (You have to  run
        it on your SYS: patition if it is going to install  the  mouse
        driver properly.
        You  proberly  want  to  include  it  in your startup-sequence,
        consult your amiga manual how to do that.

@ENDNODE

@NODE usage


        USAGE

        MOUSE <mouse type>

              <mouse type> = 1 Standard Amiga mouse (original A500) 
                             2 Nimbus mouse
                             3 Jin-Mouse
                             4 G I Mouse
                             5 G I Optical mouse
                             6 Other Optical mouses
                             7 Boing mouse
                             8 New standard Amiga mouse (original A4000)
                             9 Any track ball
                            10 Fancy Mouse (transparent cover)
                            11 Any three button mouse
                            12 Any other mouse

@ENDNODE

