@NODE history

1.1     Fixed a bug which caused my girlfriend to leave me (that bug
        succeeded with what I had tried to do for months)

1.122   Fixed a little silly bug which caused the pointer to go backwards.

2.0     Totally rewritten the code, because the compiled code of version 1.22
        was too big (1,3 MB)

2.1     Fixed a user interface with a lot of buttons.

2.2     Removed the user interface because the buttons didn't do anything.

2.3     Bug fix. When I removed the user interface I accidentaly removed some
        other code, so when you started mouse it removed the pointer.

2.4     Internal release.

3.0     Completely rewritten the code again. Now mouse is 2000% faster.

3.1     Included a Hires (660 * 530 * 16) Screen shot of my workbench
        screen which is shown at startup.

3.2     Slowed down the code a bit (the mouse has been much too fast
        since version 3.0, now it's back to normal speed)

3.3     ????

3.4     Removed the screen shot (It was too hard to update the program every
        time I changed anything on my WB)

3.5     At last now it works with WB 1.3 !!!!

3.6     Removed another bug (Who is putting in all those errors in my
        code, I have to take a chat with my cat!)

3.7     Remembered that I didn't have any cat (after I had tired to talk to
        it for an hour)

4.0     Had nothing to do so I just changed the version number.

5.0     Added the actual mouse driver code to the mouse code. So now this
        program actually works!

5.1     Removed the mouse driver code again (It was too boring)

5.2     Fixed something, I don't remember what.

5.9     Added the standard mouse (so now the standard amiga mouse works with
        it)

5.3     Oops the last version number was wrong.

6.0     Now it works with WB 2.0+

6.1     Included colors in the output copyright text

7.0     Another boring day with a new version number

7.06    Added a lot of mouses.

7.062   Included version string

7.099   Fixed nothing

7.1     Now it's returns 0 if the instalation worked properly.

7.12    Now the archive includes a AmigaGuide version of the 
        documentation

@ENDNODE


